arcade.potts.agent.cell

Class PottsCellFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • arcade.potts.agent.cell.PottsCellFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CellFactory

    public final class PottsCellFactory
extends java.lang.Object
implements CellFactory
    Implementation of CellFactory for PottsCell agents.

    For a given Series, the factory parses out parameter values into a series of maps from population to the parameter values. These maps are then combined with a PottsCellContainer to instantiate a PottsCell agent.

      • createCells

        public void createCells(Series series)
        Creates cell containers from population settings.

        For each population specified in the given series, containers are created until the population size is met. Containers are assigned regions if they exist.

        Specified by:
        createCells in interface CellFactory
        Parameters:
        series - the simulation series

        public void initialize(Series series,
                       ec.util.MersenneTwisterFast random)
        Initializes the factory for the given series.

        Regardless of loader, the population settings are parsed to get critical, values used for instantiating cells.

        initialize in interface CellFactory

      • loadCells

        public void loadCells(Series series)
        Loads cell containers into the factory container.

        Population sizes are determined from the given series. The list of loaded containers is filtered by population code and population size so that extra containers are discarded.

        Specified by:
        loadCells in interface CellFactory
